15 (5) An interim board of a new independent district may request a waiver of the
16 timeline established in subsection (4) of this section to the commissioner of
17 education or designee, except that no waiver shall be granted to alter the deadline
18 established in subsection (4)(h) of this section. The commissioner or designee
19 shall approve or deny the request within five (5) days of the submission. In
20 approving a waiver, the commissioner or designee shall establish a new deadline
21 that would reasonably ensure the new independent school district is fully
22 operational by the second July 1 following the establishment of the new
23 independent school district. A denial may be appealed to the Kentucky Board of
24 Education at its next regular meeting.
